<li><a href='http://feeds.reuters.com/~r/reuters/topNews/~3/sv81i1rM67I/story01.htm' target="_blank">EU leaders rebuff calls for action on Europe's migration crisis</a><br />
BRUSSELS (Reuters) - European Union leaders rebuffed calls from southern European states on Friday for emergency action to tackle a wave of illegal migration from Africa despite the deaths of hundreds of people in Mediterranean boat disasters.
<li><a href='http://feeds.reuters.com/~r/reuters/topNews/~3/BsNT0xRlS9c/story01.htm' target="_blank">Egyptian police use teargas after clashes in Alexandria and Suez</a><br />
CAIRO (Reuters) - Police used teargas on Friday to disperse demonstrations by supporters of ousted Islamist president Mohamed Mursi in Egypt's second city, Alexandria, and in Suez.
<li><a href='http://feeds.reuters.com/~r/reuters/topNews/~3/d4cPFv3gfyU/story01.htm' target="_blank">U.S. durable goods orders, sentiment suggest politics hurting economy</a><br />
WASHINGTON (Reuters) - Orders for a wide range of U.S.-made capital goods plummeted in September and consumer sentiment weakened sharply in October, signs that a budget battle in Washington has held back the economy.
<li><a href='http://feeds.reuters.com/~r/reuters/topNews/~3/mSgNi8ynYA0/story01.htm' target="_blank">Iraq to press U.S. on drones, F-16s to fight al Qaeda</a><br />
BAGHDAD (Reuters) - The Baghdad government wants the immediate delivery of U.S. drones and F-16 fighter jets in order to combat al Qaeda insurgents, who are making swift advances in the west of the Iraq, a senior Iraqi security official said.
